 0224                finalApCost = 5;
 0225            }
 0226        }
 227
 228        // Check for Pragmatic
 0229        if (ability.abilityType == AbilityDataSO.AbilityType.RangedAttack &&
 230            entity.myPassiveManager.pragmatic)
 0231        {
 0232            finalApCost -= 5;
 233
 234            // dont reduce ability cost below 5 energy
 0235            if (finalApCost < 5)
 0236            {
 0237                finalApCost = 5;
 0238            }
 0239        }
 240
 241        // Check for Fury
 0242        if (ability.abilityType == AbilityDataSO.AbilityType.MeleeAttack &&
 243            entity.meleeAbilityActionsTakenThisActivation == 0 &&
 244            entity.myPassiveManager.fury)
 0245        {
 0246            finalApCost = 0;
 0247        }
 248
 249        // Check for Grace
 0250        if (ability.abilityType == AbilityDataSO.AbilityType.Skill &&
 251            entity.skillAbilityActionsTakenThisActivation == 0 &&
 252            entity.myPassiveManager.grace)
 0253        {
 0254            finalApCost = 0;
 0255        }
 256
 257        // Check for Pragmatic
 0258        if (ability.abilityType == AbilityDataSO.AbilityType.RangedAttack &&
 259            entity.rangedAttackAbilityActionsTakenThisActivation == 0 &&
 260            entity.myPassiveManager.pragmatic)
 0261        {
 0262            finalApCost = 0;
 0263        }
 264
 265        // Check for Preparation
 0266        if (entity.myPassiveManager.preparation && ability.abilityName != "Preparation" &&
 267            ability.abilityName != "Slice And Dice" &&
 268            ability.abilityName != "Super Conductor" &&
 269            ability.abilityName != "Rapid Fire")
 0270        {
 0271            entity.myPassiveManager.ModifyPreparation(-entity.myPassiveManager.preparationStacks);
 0272            finalApCost = 0;
 0273        }
 274
 275        // Check for Flux passive
 0276        if (ability.abilityName == "Move")
 0277        {
 278            // if character has a free move available
 0279            if (entity.moveActionsTakenThisActivation == 0 && entity.myPassiveManager.flux)
 0280            {
 0281                finalApCost = 0;
 0282            }
 0283        }
 284
 285        // Check 'spend X energy' abilities
 0286        if (ability.abilityName == "Slice And Dice" ||
 287            ability.abilityName == "Rapid Fire" ||
 288             ability.abilityName == "Super Conductor")
 0289        {
 0290            finalApCost = entity.currentEnergy;
 0291        }
 292
 293        // Check 'Expert Marksman' state and Shoot ability
 0294        if(entity.defender &&
 295            ability.abilityName == "Shoot" &&
 296            StateManager.Instance.DoesPlayerAlreadyHaveState("Expert Marksman"))
 0297        {
 0298            finalApCost = 10;
 0299        }
 300
 301        // Check 'Blood Lust' state and Strike/Twin Strike ability
 0302        if (entity.defender &&
 303            (ability.abilityName == "Strike" || ability.abilityName == "Twin Strike") &&
 304            StateManager.Instance.DoesPlayerAlreadyHaveState("Blood Lust"))
 0305        {
 0306            finalApCost = 10;
 0307        }
 308
 0309        Debug.Log("AbilityLogic.CalculateAbilityEnergyCost() returning " + finalApCost.ToString() +
 310            " as the final energy cost of " + ability.abilityName + " used by " + entity.myName);
 311
 0312        return finalApCost;
 0313    }
 314    public int CalculateAbilityRange(Ability ability, LivingEntity entity)
 0315    {
 0316        Debug.Log("AbilityLogic.CalculateAbilityRange() called for " +
 317            entity.myName + " using ability " + ability.abilityName);
 318
 0319        int rangeReturned = 0;
 320
 0321        if (ability.abilityType == AbilityDataSO.AbilityType.RangedAttack)
 0322        {
 0323            rangeReturned = EntityLogic.GetTotalRangeOfRangedAttack(entity, ability);
 0324        }
 0325        else if (ability.abilityType == AbilityDataSO.AbilityType.MeleeAttack)
 0326        {
 0327            rangeReturned = entity.currentMeleeRange;
 0328        }
 0329        else if (ability.abilityType == AbilityDataSO.AbilityType.Skill)
 0330        {
 0331            rangeReturned = ability.abilityRange;
 0332        }
 0333        else if (ability.abilityType == AbilityDataSO.AbilityType.Power)
 0334        {
 0335            rangeReturned = 0;
 0336        }
 337        else
 0338        {
 0339            rangeReturned = 0;
 0340        }
 341
 0342        Debug.Log("AbilityLogic.CalculateAbilityRange() final range of " + ability.abilityName +
 343            " used by " + entity.myName + " is: " + rangeReturned.ToString());
 344
 0345        return rangeReturned;
 0346    }

 426    private IEnumerator PerformStrikeCoroutine(LivingEntity caster, LivingEntity victim, OldCoroutineData action)
 0427    {
 428        // Set up properties
 0429        Ability strike = caster.mySpellBook.GetAbilityByName("Strike");
 0430        bool critical = CombatLogic.Instance.RollForCritical(caster, victim, strike);
 0431        bool parry = CombatLogic.Instance.RollForParry(victim, caster);
 0432        string damageType = CombatLogic.Instance.CalculateFinalDamageTypeOfAttack(caster, strike, caster.myMainHandWeapo
 0433        int finalDamageValue = CombatLogic.Instance.GetFinalDamageValueAfterAllCalculations(caster, victim, strike, dama
 434
 435        // Status VFX notification for enemies
 0436        if (caster.enemy)
 0437        {
 0438            VisualEffectManager.Instance.CreateStatusEffect(caster.transform.position, "Strike");
 0439            yield return new WaitForSeconds(0.5f);
 0440        }
 441
 442        // Pay energy cost, + etc
 0443        OnAbilityUsedStart(strike, caster);
 444
 445        // Play attack animation
 0446        caster.StartCoroutine(caster.PlayMeleeAttackAnimation(victim));
 447
 448        // if the target successfully parried, dont do HandleDamage: do parry stuff instead
 0449        if (parry)
 0450        {
 0451            OldCoroutineData parryAction = CombatLogic.Instance.HandleParry(caster, victim);
 0452            yield return new WaitUntil(() => parryAction.ActionResolved() == true);
 0453        }
 454
 455        // if the target did not parry, handle damage event normally
 456        else
 0457        {
 0458            if (critical)
 0459            {
 0460                VisualEffectManager.Instance.CreateStatusEffect(caster.transform.position, "CRITICAL!");
 0461            }
 0462            OldCoroutineData abilityAction = CombatLogic.Instance.HandleDamage(finalDamageValue, caster, victim, damageT
 0463            yield return new WaitUntil(() => abilityAction.ActionResolved() == true);
 0464        }
 465
 466        // remove camoflage, etc
 0467        OnAbilityUsedFinish(strike, caster);
 0468        action.coroutineCompleted = true;
 469
 0470    }

 1201    private IEnumerator PerformBladeFlurryCoroutine(LivingEntity caster, OldCoroutineData action)
 01202    {
 1203        // Set up properties
 01204        Ability bladeFlurry = caster.mySpellBook.GetAbilityByName("Blade Flurry");
 01205        string damageType = CombatLogic.Instance.CalculateFinalDamageTypeOfAttack(caster, bladeFlurry, caster.myMainHand

 1207
 1208        // Status VFX notification for enemies
 01209        if (caster.enemy)
 01210        {
 01211            VisualEffectManager.Instance.CreateStatusEffect(caster.transform.position, "Blade Flurry");
 01212            yield return new WaitForSeconds(0.5f);
 01213        }
 1214
 1215        // Pay energy cost
 01216        OnAbilityUsedStart(bladeFlurry, caster);
 1217
 01218        for (int attacksMade = 0; attacksMade < 3; attacksMade++)
 01219        {
 1220            // check make sure character didnt get killed by something like thorns/riposte mid loop
 1221            // if they did, break
 01222            if (caster.inDeathProcess)
 01223            {
 01224                Debug.Log("AbilityLogic.PerformBladeFlurryCoroutine() detected that the caster was killed mid loop, brea
 01225                break;
 1226            }
 1227
 01228            int listIndex = 0;
 01229            LivingEntity nextTarget = null;
 1230
 1231            // Calculate which target will be hit next
 01232            if (targetsInRange.Count > 1)
 01233            {
 01234                listIndex = Random.Range(0, targetsInRange.Count - 1);
 01235            }
 01236            else if(targetsInRange.Count == 1)
 01237            {
 01238                listIndex = 0;
 01239            }
 1240            else
 01241            {
 01242                Debug.Log("AbilityLogic.PerformBladeFlurryCoroutine() detected that there are no more valid targets to h
 01243                break;
 1244            }
 1245
 1246            // Set target
 01247            nextTarget = targetsInRange[listIndex];
 1248
 1249            // Start attack on target
 01250            if(caster != null && nextTarget != null && nextTarget.inDeathProcess == false)
 01251            {
 01252                bool critical = CombatLogic.Instance.RollForCritical(caster, nextTarget, bladeFlurry);
 01253                bool parry = CombatLogic.Instance.RollForParry(nextTarget, caster);
 01254                int finalDamageValue = CombatLogic.Instance.GetFinalDamageValueAfterAllCalculations(caster, nextTarget, 
 1255
 1256                // Play attack animation
 01257                caster.StartCoroutine(caster.PlayMeleeAttackAnimation(nextTarget));
 1258
 1259                // if the target successfully parried, dont do HandleDamage: do parry stuff instead
 01260                if (parry)
 01261                {
 01262                    OldCoroutineData parryAction = CombatLogic.Instance.HandleParry(caster, nextTarget);
 01263                    yield return new WaitUntil(() => parryAction.ActionResolved() == true);
 01264                }

 1266                // if the target did not parry, handle damage event normally
 1267                else
 01268                {
 01269                    if (critical)
 01270                    {
 01271                        VisualEffectManager.Instance.CreateStatusEffect(caster.transform.position, "CRITICAL!");
 01272                    }
 01273                    OldCoroutineData abilityAction = CombatLogic.Instance.HandleDamage(finalDamageValue, caster, nextTar
 01274                    yield return new WaitUntil(() => abilityAction.ActionResolved() == true);
 01275                }
 01276            }
 01277        }

 01280        OnAbilityUsedFinish(bladeFlurry, caster);

 01285    }

 1557
 1558        // If target has 30% or less health, they are killed instantly
 01559        if ((victim.currentMaxHealth * 0.3f) >= victim.currentHealth)
 01560        {
 01561            instantKill = true;
 01562        }
 1563
 1564        // Pay energy cost, + etc
 01565        OnAbilityUsedStart(decapitate, caster);
 1566
 1567        // Play attack animation
 01568        caster.StartCoroutine(caster.PlayMeleeAttackAnimation(victim));
 1569
 1570        // if the target successfully parried, dont do HandleDamage: do parry stuff instead
 01571        if (parry)
 01572        {
 01573            OldCoroutineData parryAction = CombatLogic.Instance.HandleParry(caster, victim);
 01574            yield return new WaitUntil(() => parryAction.ActionResolved() == true);
 01575        }
 1576
 1577        // if the target did not parry, handle damage event normally
 1578        else
 01579        {
 01580            if (critical)
 01581            {
 01582                VisualEffectManager.Instance.CreateStatusEffect(caster.transform.position, "CRITICAL!");
 01583            }
 01584            OldCoroutineData abilityAction = CombatLogic.Instance.HandleDamage(finalDamageValue, caster, victim, damageT
 01585            yield return new WaitUntil(() => abilityAction.ActionResolved() == true);
 1586
 01587            if(!victim.inDeathProcess && instantKill)
 01588            {
 1589                // the victim was insta killed, start death process
 01590                VisualEffectManager.Instance.CreateStatusEffect(victim.transform.position, "DECAPITATED!");
 01591                victim.inDeathProcess = true;
 01592                victim.StopAllCoroutines();
 01593                CombatLogic.Instance.HandleDeath(victim);
 01594            }
 01595        }
 1596
 1597        // remove camoflage, etc
 01598        OnAbilityUsedFinish(decapitate, caster);
 01599        action.coroutineCompleted = true;
 1600
 01601    }

 02051        int attacksToMake = caster.currentEnergy / 10;

 2053

 2063

 02100        }

 2102        // remove camoflage, etc

 2514    private IEnumerator PerformShieldSlamCoroutine(LivingEntity caster, LivingEntity victim, OldCoroutineData action)
 02515    {
 2516        // Set up properties
 02517        Ability shieldSlam = caster.mySpellBook.GetAbilityByName("Shield Slam");
 02518        bool critical = CombatLogic.Instance.RollForCritical(caster, victim, shieldSlam);
 02519        bool parry = CombatLogic.Instance.RollForParry(victim, caster);
 02520        string damageType = CombatLogic.Instance.CalculateFinalDamageTypeOfAttack(caster, shieldSlam, caster.myMainHandW
 02521        int finalDamageValue = CombatLogic.Instance.GetFinalDamageValueAfterAllCalculations(caster, victim, shieldSlam, 
 2522
 2523        // Status VFX notification for enemies
 02524        if (caster.enemy)
 02525        {
 02526            VisualEffectManager.Instance.CreateStatusEffect(caster.transform.position, "Shield Slam");
 02527            yield return new WaitForSeconds(0.5f);
 02528        }
 2529
 2530        // Pay energy cost, + etc
 02531        OnAbilityUsedStart(shieldSlam, caster);
 2532
 2533        // Play attack animation
 02534        caster.StartCoroutine(caster.PlayMeleeAttackAnimation(victim));
 2535
 2536        // if the target successfully parried, dont do HandleDamage: do parry stuff instead
 02537        if (parry)
 02538        {
 02539            OldCoroutineData parryAction = CombatLogic.Instance.HandleParry(caster, victim);
 02540            yield return new WaitUntil(() => parryAction.ActionResolved() == true);
 02541        }
 2542

 2544        else
 02545        {
 02546            if (critical)
 02547            {
 02548                VisualEffectManager.Instance.CreateStatusEffect(caster.transform.position, "CRITICAL!");
 02549            }
 02550            OldCoroutineData abilityAction = CombatLogic.Instance.HandleDamage(finalDamageValue, caster, victim, damageT
 02551            yield return new WaitUntil(() => abilityAction.ActionResolved() == true);

 02554            if (victim.inDeathProcess == false)
 02555            {
 02556                MovementLogic.Instance.KnockBackEntity(caster, victim, shieldSlam.abilityPrimaryValue);
 02557                yield return new WaitForSeconds(0.5f);
 02558            }
 02559        }
 2560
 2561        // remove camoflage, etc
 02562        OnAbilityUsedFinish(shieldSlam, caster);
 02563        action.coroutineCompleted = true;
 2564
 02565    }

 2639

 02678        }

 3043    private IEnumerator PerformChillingBlowCoroutine(LivingEntity caster, LivingEntity target, OldCoroutineData action)
 03044    {
 3045        // Set up properties
 03046        Ability chillingBlow = caster.mySpellBook.GetAbilityByName("Chilling Blow");
 03047        bool critical = CombatLogic.Instance.RollForCritical(caster, target, chillingBlow);
 03048        bool parry = CombatLogic.Instance.RollForParry(target, caster);
 03049        string damageType = CombatLogic.Instance.CalculateFinalDamageTypeOfAttack(caster, chillingBlow, caster.myMainHan
 03050        int finalDamageValue = CombatLogic.Instance.GetFinalDamageValueAfterAllCalculations(caster, target, chillingBlow
 3051
 3052        // Status VFX notification for enemies
 03053        if (caster.enemy)
 03054        {
 03055            VisualEffectManager.Instance.CreateStatusEffect(caster.transform.position, "Chilling Blow");
 03056            yield return new WaitForSeconds(0.5f);
 03057        }
 3058
 3059        // Pay energy cost, + etc
 03060        OnAbilityUsedStart(chillingBlow, caster);
 3061
 3062        // Play attack animation
 03063        caster.StartCoroutine(caster.PlayMeleeAttackAnimation(target));
 03064        yield return new WaitForSeconds(0.2f);
 03065        VisualEffectManager.Instance.CreateSmallFrostExplosion(target.transform.position);
 3066
 3067        // if the target successfully parried, dont do HandleDamage: do parry stuff instead
 03068        if (parry)
 03069        {
 03070            OldCoroutineData parryAction = CombatLogic.Instance.HandleParry(caster, target);
 03071            yield return new WaitUntil(() => parryAction.ActionResolved() == true);
 03072        }
 3073
 3074        // if the target did not parry, handle damage event normally
 3075        else
 03076        {
 03077            if (critical)
 03078            {
 03079                VisualEffectManager.Instance.CreateStatusEffect(caster.transform.position, "CRITICAL!");
 03080            }
 03081            OldCoroutineData abilityAction = CombatLogic.Instance.HandleDamage(finalDamageValue, caster, target, damageT
 03082            yield return new WaitUntil(() => abilityAction.ActionResolved() == true);
 3083
 3084            // Apply Immobilized if chilled
 03085            if (target.inDeathProcess == false &&
 3086                target.myPassiveManager.chilled)
 03087            {
 03088                target.myPassiveManager.ModifyImmobilized(1);
 03089                yield return new WaitForSeconds(0.5f);
 03090            }
 03091        }
 3092
 3093        // remove camoflage, etc
 03094        OnAbilityUsedFinish(chillingBlow, caster);
 03095        action.coroutineCompleted = true;
 03096    }

 03494        return action;

 3496    private IEnumerator PerformGlacialBurstCoroutine(LivingEntity caster, OldCoroutineData action)
 03497    {
 3498        // Set up properties
 03499        Ability glacialBurst = caster.mySpellBook.GetAbilityByName("Glacial Burst");
 03500        string damageType = CombatLogic.Instance.CalculateFinalDamageTypeOfAttack(caster, glacialBurst);
 03501        List<LivingEntity> targetsInRange = EntityLogic.GetAllEnemiesWithinRange(caster, caster.currentMeleeRange);
 03502        List<LivingEntity> targetsHit = new List<LivingEntity>();
 3503
 3504        // Status VFX notification for enemies
 03505        if (caster.enemy)
 03506        {
 03507            VisualEffectManager.Instance.CreateStatusEffect(caster.transform.position, "Glacial Burst");
 03508            yield return new WaitForSeconds(0.5f);
 03509        }
 3510
 3511        // Play animation
 03512        caster.PlaySkillAnimation();
 3513
 3514        // get a random target 3 times
 03515        for (int i = 0; i < glacialBurst.abilitySecondaryValue; i++)
 03516        {
 03517            targetsHit.Add(targetsInRange[Random.Range(0, targetsInRange.Count)]);
 03518        }
 3519
 3520        // Pay energy cost
 03521        OnAbilityUsedStart(glacialBurst, caster);
 3522
 3523        // Resolve hits against targets
 03524        foreach (LivingEntity entity in targetsHit)
 03525        {
 03526            if (entity.inDeathProcess == false)
 03527            {
 03528                bool critical = CombatLogic.Instance.RollForCritical(caster, entity, glacialBurst);
 03529                bool dodge = CombatLogic.Instance.RollForDodge(entity, caster);
 03530                int finalDamageValue = CombatLogic.Instance.GetFinalDamageValueAfterAllCalculations(caster, entity, glac
 3531
 3532                // Play attack animation
 03533                caster.StartCoroutine(caster.PlayMeleeAttackAnimation(entity));
 3534
 3535                // Create frost bolt VFX
 03536                OldCoroutineData frostBoltAction = VisualEffectManager.Instance.ShootToonFrostBall(caster.tile.WorldPosi
 03537                yield return new WaitUntil(() => frostBoltAction.ActionResolved() == true);
 3538
 3539                // if the target successfully dodged, dont do HandleDamage: do dodge stuff instead
 03540                if (dodge)
 03541                {
 03542                    OldCoroutineData dodgeAction = CombatLogic.Instance.HandleDodge(caster, entity);
 03543                    yield return new WaitUntil(() => dodgeAction.ActionResolved() == true);
 03544                }
 3545
 3546                // if the target did not parry, handle damage event normally
 3547                else
 03548                {
 03549                    if (critical)
 03550                    {
 03551                        VisualEffectManager.Instance.CreateStatusEffect(caster.transform.position, "CRITICAL!");
 03552                    }
 03553                    OldCoroutineData abilityAction = CombatLogic.Instance.HandleDamage(finalDamageValue, caster, entity,
 03554                    yield return new WaitUntil(() => abilityAction.ActionResolved() == true);
 03555                }
 3556
 03557            }
 3558
 03559        }
 3560
 3561        // Remove camo + etc
 03562        OnAbilityUsedFinish(glacialBurst, caster);
 3563
 3564        // Resolve/Complete event
 03565        action.coroutineCompleted = true;
 3566
 03567    }

 04992        yield return new WaitUntil(() => holyFireHit.ActionResolved() == true);
 4993

 04998        }

 5001        else

 05005            bool dodge = CombatLogic.Instance.RollForDodge(target, caster);
 05006            string damageType = CombatLogic.Instance.CalculateFinalDamageTypeOfAttack(caster, holyFire);
 05007            int finalDamageValue = CombatLogic.Instance.GetFinalDamageValueAfterAllCalculations(caster, target, holyFire
 5008
 5009

 05014                yield return new WaitUntil(() => dodgeAction.ActionResolved() == true);
 05015            }
 5016

 05021                {
 05022                    VisualEffectManager.Instance.CreateStatusEffect(caster.transform.position, "CRITICAL!");
 05023                }
 05024                OldCoroutineData abilityAction = CombatLogic.Instance.HandleDamage(finalDamageValue, caster, target, dam
 05025                yield return new WaitUntil(() => abilityAction.ActionResolved() == true);
 05026            }
 05027        }
 5028

 05031        action.coroutineCompleted = true;

 05052            yield return new WaitForSeconds(0.5f);
 05053        }
 5054
 5055        // Play animation
 05056        caster.PlaySkillAnimation();

 5060

 05062        OnAbilityUsedStart(blindingLight, caster);
 5063
 5064        // Resolve damage against targets hit
 05065        foreach (LivingEntity entity in targetsInBlastRadius)
 05066        {
 05067            bool critical = CombatLogic.Instance.RollForCritical(caster, entity, blindingLight);
 05068            int finalDamageValue = CombatLogic.Instance.GetFinalDamageValueAfterAllCalculations(caster, entity, blinding
 5069

 05073            }

 05077        }
 5078
 5079        // Brief delay between damage VFX and Blind VFX
 05080        yield return new WaitForSeconds(0.5f);
 5081
 5082        // Blind all targets hit
 05083        foreach (LivingEntity entity in targetsInBlastRadius)
 05084        {

 05089            }
 05090        }

 5093
 05094    }

 5747

 05750        {
 05751            targetsHit.Add(targetsInRange[Random.Range(0, targetsInRange.Count)]);
 05752        }
 5753
 5754        // Pay energy cost
 05755        OnAbilityUsedStart(unbridledChaos, caster);
 5756

 05758        foreach (LivingEntity entity in targetsHit)
 05759        {
 05760            if (entity.inDeathProcess == false)
 05761            {
 05762                bool critical = CombatLogic.Instance.RollForCritical(caster, entity, unbridledChaos);
 05763                bool dodge = CombatLogic.Instance.RollForDodge(entity, caster);
 05764                int finalDamageValue = CombatLogic.Instance.GetFinalDamageValueAfterAllCalculations(caster, entity, unbr
 5765

 05771                yield return new WaitUntil(() => shootAction.ActionResolved() == true);

 05774                if (dodge)

 05776                    OldCoroutineData dodgeAction = CombatLogic.Instance.HandleDodge(caster, entity);
 05777                    yield return new WaitUntil(() => dodgeAction.ActionResolved() == true);
 05778                }

 5780                // if the target did not parry, handle damage event normally
 5781                else
 05782                {

 05784                    {

 05788                    yield return new WaitUntil(() => abilityAction.ActionResolved() == true);

 05793        }
